21 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF ARKANSAS:
22
23 SECTION 1. Arkansas Code Title 16, Chapter 90, Subchapter 3, is
24 amended to add an additional section to read as follows:
25 16-90-312. Restitution for victims of human trafficking.
26 (a) A person convicted of any violation of the Human Trafficking Act
27 of 2013, ยง 5-18-101 et seq., shall be ordered to pay mandatory restitution to
28 the victim or other entity, as appropriate, including without limitation:
29 (1) Costs of medical and psychological treatment, including
30 physical and occupational therapy and rehabilitation;
31 (2) Costs of necessary transportation, temporary housing, and
32 child care;
33 (3) Cost of the investigation and prosecution and other court-
34 related costs such as victim advocate fees;
35 (4) Return of property, cost of damage to property, or full
36 value of property if destroyed or damaged beyond repair;
